SIMPLE: counterbrace
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Counterbrace
<hw>Coun"ter*brace`</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Naut.)</fld> <def>To brace in opposite directions; <as>as, to
<ex>counterbrace</ex> the yards, <it>i. e.</it>, to brace the head yards
one way and the after yards another</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Engin.)</fld> <def>To brace in such a way that
opposite strains are resisted; to apply counter braces to.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Counterbuff</ent>⟦br⟧
